    <briefdescription>
<para>Named-value table that allows unique names and repeated values. </para>
    </briefdescription>
    <detaileddescription>
<para>A key may appear only once in the table. Setting an existing key updates the stored value. The same value may be stored under multiple different keys.</para>
<para>This is useful for maps where one name must resolve to one current value, but several names may intentionally share that value.</para>
<para><parameterlist kind="templateparam"><parameteritem>
<parameternamelist>
<parametername>TValue</parametername>
</parameternamelist>
<parameterdescription>
<para>Type of the stored values. </para>
</parameterdescription>
</parameteritem>
</parameterlist>
</para>
    </detaileddescription>
